<subSubSection id="D9A56571772FFFD4FF62CC17FD3FF9E2" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="910036FA772FFFD4FF62CC17FD3FF9E2" blockId="3.[151,1437,1562,2022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FF62CC17FE99F9AA" bold="true" box="[199,334,1562,1587]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Etymology.</emphasis>
In naming this new genus 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FDDECC17FCD2F9AB" authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[635,773,1562,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FDDECC17FCD2F9AB" box="[635,773,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">BernadOttea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we honor the Head of the Royal House of Bernadotte, His Majesty The King of 
<collectingCountry id="E9A8766A772FFFD4FE2ACC33FE3FF9CE" box="[399,488,1598,1623]" name="Sweden" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Sweden</collectingCountry>
Carl XVI Gustaf for his commitment as the President of the Council of the World Wide Fund For Nature (
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FE01CC6FFDAFF9E3" box="[420,632,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">VärldsnaturFOnden</emphasis>
) 
<collectingCountry id="E9A8766A772FFFD4FD2DCC6FFD33F9E2" box="[648,740,1634,1659]" name="Sweden" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Sweden</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9A56571772FFFD3FF62CC8BFDD2FF6E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="533" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="910036FA772FFFD3FF62CC8BFDD2FF6E" blockId="3.[151,1437,1562,2022]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="533" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FF62CC8BFE9BF906" bold="true" box="[199,332,1670,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Discussion.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FE71CC8BFD88F907" authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[468,607,1670,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FE71CC8BFD88F907" box="[468,607,1670,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">BernadOttea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is no doubt a monophyletic group. The included species share uniquely derived character states, such as the gonocoxites provided with multiple processes, and all of the tegmen, ejaculatory apodeme and aedeagal bulge closely interlinked to form complicated, strongly sclerotized structures. The only other winnertziine whose tegmen deviates from the simple, subtrapezoid to subtriangular outline typical of the tribe is 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FE94CD1BFD1AF8B6" authority="Jaschhof, 2013" authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2013" box="[305,717,1814,1839]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ekmanomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="svecica">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FE94CD1BFDCAF8B7" box="[305,541,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">EkmanOmyia svecica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F52E4B0B772FFFD4FD86CD1BFD1AF8B6" box="[547,717,1814,1839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" refId="ref4237" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article">Jaschhof, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but its similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FC68CD1BFB8FF8B7" authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[973,1112,1814,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FC68CD1BFB8FF8B7" box="[973,1112,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">BernadOttea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is merely superficial and not supported by conformity in other genitalic structures (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="F52E4B0B772FFFD4FCE5CD37FBAEF8CA" box="[832,1145,1850,1875]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" refId="ref4237" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 28). 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FB56CD36FAA9F8CA" authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2018" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2018" box="[1267,1406,1851,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Bernadottea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FB56CD36FAA9F8CA" box="[1267,1406,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">BernadOttea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is possibly the only monophyletic group of 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FDC6CD53FD27F8EE" authorityName="Panelius" authorityYear="1965" box="[611,752,1886,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Winnertziini">Winnertziini</taxonomicName>
in which vein M4 is consistently lacking. The same character state was regarded as constitutive of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FD08CD8BFC9AF804" authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1920" box="[685,845,1926,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Parwinnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FD08CD8BFC9AF804" box="[685,845,1926,1949]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Parwinnertzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which contains one species each in North America and Europe, but these two species are largely dissimilar in other respects and, more importantly, not fundamentally different from 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD4FE99CDC3FE62F87C" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1860" box="[316,437,1998,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Winnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FE99CDC3FE62F87C" box="[316,437,1998,2021]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Winnertzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="F52E4B0B772FFFD4FE4ECDC3FCDDF87F" box="[491,778,1997,2022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" refId="ref4275" refString="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Zaitzev, A. I. (1998) New species of gall midges of formerly monotypic genera (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae: Porricondylinae). International Journal of Dipterological ReSearch, 9, 85 - 89." type="journal article">Mamaev &amp; Zaitzev 1998</bibRefCitation>
). The genitalia of male 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D79772FFFD3FBB3CDC3FEE5FF29" authority="Mamaev &amp; Zaitzev, 1998" authorityName="Mamaev &amp; Zaitzev" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Parwinnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="533" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="italiana">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE8772FFFD4FBB3CDC3FAC2F87C" box="[1046,1301,1997,2021]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Parwinnertzia italiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F52E4B0B772FFFD3FAB9CDC3FEE5FF29" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="533" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" refId="ref4275" refString="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Zaitzev, A. I. (1998) New species of gall midges of formerly monotypic genera (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae: Porricondylinae). International Journal of Dipterological ReSearch, 9, 85 - 89." type="journal article">Mamaev &amp; Zaitzev, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
correspond to the structure found typically in 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D797728FFD3FCF7CA95FC1CFF36" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1860" box="[850,971,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Winnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE87728FFD3FCF7CA95FC1CFF36" box="[850,971,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Winnertzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F52E4B0B7728FFD3FC79CA95FA88FF29" box="[988,1375,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" refId="ref4275" refString="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Zaitzev, A. I. (1998) New species of gall midges of formerly monotypic genera (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae: Porricondylinae). International Journal of Dipterological ReSearch, 9, 85 - 89." type="journal article">Mamaev &amp; Zaitzev 1998: fig. 11</bibRefCitation>
). We assume that a taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D797728FFD3FDC0CAB1FD23FF4C" authorityName="Panelius" authorityYear="1965" box="[613,756,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Winnertziini">Winnertziini</taxonomicName>
, if done on a global scale, would result in subsuming 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D797728FFD3FF32CAEDFEE0FF6E" authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1920" box="[151,311,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Parwinnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE87728FFD3FF32CAEDFEE0FF6E" box="[151,311,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Parwinnertzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="56BF4D797728FFD3FE20CAEDFE29FF6E" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1860" box="[389,510,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Winnertzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3CBEAE87728FFD3FE20CAEDFE29FF6E" box="[389,510,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Winnertzia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
